
[1]kettle

   KET'TLE, n. A vessel of iron or other metal, with a wide mouth, usually
   without a cover, used for heating and boiling water or other liquor.

   Among the Tartars, a kettle represents a family, or as many as feed
   from one kettle.

   Among the Dutch, a battery of mortars sunk in the earth, is called a
   kettle.
